Williams n 1: United States country singer and songwriter (1923-1953) [syn: {Hank Williams}, {Hiram Williams}, {Hiram King Williams}] 2: English philosopher credited with reviving the field of moral philosophy (1929-2003) [syn: {Sir Bernanrd Williams}, {Bernanrd Arthur Owen Williams}] 3: United States poet (1883-1963) [syn: {William Carlos Williams}] 4: United States baseball player noted as a hitter (1918-2002) [syn: {Ted Williams}, {Theodore Samuel Williams}] 5: English clergyman and colonist who was expelled from Massachusetts for criticizing Puritanism; he founded Providence in 1636 and obtained a royal charter for Rhode Island in 1663 (1603-1683) [syn: {Roger Williams}] 6: United States playwright (1911-1983) [syn: {Tennessee Williams}, {Thomas Lanier Williams}]
